ional Dialogue process. By combining in-person & online sessions with the #MekekerEthiopia digital campaign, we ensured their voices reached the highest levels of government.",impact:"Submitted 80+ grassroots issues to the Ethiopian National Dialogue Commission for official agenda framing."},{title:"Bridging the Gender Gap in Digital Financial Service",timeline:"January 2024 – June 2024",focus:"Research & Policy Advocacy",desc:"Our research revealed critical barriers preventing women from accessing mobile money services (MMS). We moved beyond data by developing Women-Centered Design Principles and engaging directly with the National Bank of Ethiopia (NBE) and the Commercial Bank of Ethiopia (CBE).",impact:"Catalyzed official policy dialogues with the NBE and secured a commitment from CBEbirr to redesign their services for female users. The #ClosetheGenderGap campaign mobilized a national network of advocates."},{title:"Ethiopia Digital Rights Multiplier Program",timeline:"July 2024 – December 2024",focus:"Digital Security & Human Rights",desc:'Operating in Mekelle, Dire Dawa, and Jigjiga, this program built a frontline defense for digital rights. We trained a core group of "Digital Rights Defenders," with a specific emphasis on protecting women, who are often the most vulnerable to online threats.',impact:"Developed 40 expert trainers who successfully empowered an additional 80 leaders in digital security and privacy tools."},{title:"Civil Society Innovation Fund",timeline:"September 2022 – August 2025",focus:"Digital Activism & Institutional Frameworks",desc:"This flagship three-year program spans five major cities: Addis Ababa, Dire Dawa, Assosa, Hawassa, and Bahir Dar. We are pioneering the future of civic space by helping organizations transition from traditional methods to sophisticated digital activism while ensuring ethical standards are maintained.",impact:"Capacitated 80+ media outlets and CSOs through the installation of Digital Engagement Policy frameworks and the creation of a first-of-its-kind Guideline for Ethical Digital Activism. Key Achievement: Successfully built the Emerging CSO Online Network (DERSHA.net)."},{title:"Ethiopia Digital Safety Program",timeline:"October 2025 – December 2025",focus:"Cybersecurity & Advocacy",desc:"Focusing on Addis Ababa and Arba-Minch, this program equips journalists and civil society leaders with the technical skills needed to navigate a shifting digital landscape safely.",impact:"Graduated a cohort of 40 leaders specialized in safe communication, encryption, and digital rights advocacy, with a priority focus on female empowerment."}],Fle=()=>{const t=L.useRef(null),{scrollYProgress:e}=x7({target:t,offset:["start end","end end"]}),n=X9(e,{stiffness:100,damping:30,restDelta:.001});return T.jsx(Be.div,{initial:{opacity:0},animate:{opacity:1},exit:{opacity:0},className:"min-h-screen pt-32 pb-20 px-6",children:T.jsxs("div",{className:"max-w-7xl mx-auto",children:[T.jsxs("div",{className:"text-center mb-20",children:[T.jsx("h1",{className:"font-display text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6",children:"Our Programmes"}),T.jsx("p",{className:"text-slate-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto",children:"Executing impactful initiatives that bridge the gap between technology and civic responsibility."})]}),T.jsxs("div",{ref:t,className:"relative max-w-5xl mx-auto mb-32",children:[T.jsx("div",{className:"absolute left-0 md:left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 w-px bg-white/10 md:-translate-x-1/2"}),T.jsx(Be.div,{style:{scaleY:n},className:"absolute left-0 md:left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 w-[2px] bg-gradient-to-b from-blue-500 via-purple-500 to-blue-500 shadow-[0_0_15px_rgba(59,130,246,0.6)] origin-top md:-translate-x-1/2 z-0"}),Gle.map((r,i)=>T.jsxs(Be.div,{initial:{opacity:0,y:50},whileInView:{opacity:1,y:0},viewport:{once:!0,margin:"-50px"},transition:{duration:.5,delay:i*.1},className:`relative flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 mb-16 ${i%2===0?"md:flex-row-reverse":""}`,children:[T.jsx(Be.div,{initial:{scale:0,backgroundColo